<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-83-0909 </DOCNO><TEXT>Renewable energy sources are receiving increased attention today as aresult of their high environmental compatibility. The article concernsitself with the technical status of renewable energy sources, with theirapplicability in the Federal Republic or other countries and with questionsof economics. In the area of photovoltaic energy alone, incalculabledevelopments are to be expected. The considerable inhibiting factor forrenewable energy sources however has again and again proved to be lackof economic viability. Renewable energy sources, along with fusion andbreeder reactors, are the only genuine long-term alternative for theearth's energy supply. The political decisions of today determine towhat extent these energies will be available for us in the future.</TEXT></DOC>